                    "updated": "2007-05-06T09:35:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17280",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing to 'Unassigned'",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-10-17T15:28:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-10-17T15:28:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22594",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Personally, I would move the count() out of the try block and have it as the first if (). Then clear the events after the e-mail gets sent. That way if someone called shutdown and then added more events they would get sent as well.\n\nAlso, maybe add optional header and footers would be nice too. That way you can add more then just a log of events. My need would be to make a table with other descriptions. I'll try to add a screenshot of what I typically e-mail. I'll also try to write an update to this patch for these features.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-20T11:13:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-20T11:13:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22595",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Example of what e-mails look like from my error logs. If the optional header and footer is added, I can turn the list of events into a HTML table.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-20T11:23:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-20T11:23:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22616",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok, here is what I've put together. Changes since the original patch:\n\n* Removed shutdown check, rather checks for events\n* Removed the try\/catch block, Zend_Mail will not throw exceptions anyway\n* Changed mail property access to protected (better support for extending the class)\n* Changed $mail to $_mail (seems to be the \"Zend\" way for naming protected properties)\n* Added support to add a header and footer\n* Added support to change body type to HTML\n* Added header, footer, and html properties as public, shutdown() can deal with improper values\n\nAlso, I removed my thought about multiple shutdowns, it's unlikely to happen anyway.\n\n{code}\nclass Zend_Log_Writer_Mail extends Zend_Log_Writer_Mock\n{\n\tprotected $_mail;\n\t\n\tpublic $header;\n\tpublic $footer;\n\tpublic $html;\n\t\n\tpublic function __construct(Zend_Mail $mail, $header = '', $footer = '', $html = false)\n\t{\n\t\t$this->_mail = $mail;\n\t\t$this->header = $header;\n\t\t$this->footer = $footer;\n\t\t$this->html   = $html;\n\t}\n\t\n\tpublic function shutdown()\n\t{\n\t\t\/\/ Check for events\n\t\tif (!empty($this->events)) {\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\/\/ Start body, add previous content\n\t\t\t$body  = ($this->html ? $this->_mail->getBodyHtml(true) : $this->_mail->getBodyText(true));\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\/\/ Add header, cast as string in case non-string set\n\t\t\t$body .= (string) $this->header;\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\/\/ Add each event and apply the format\n\t\t\tforeach ($this->events as $event) {\n\t\t\t\t$body .= $this->_formatter->format($event);\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\/\/ Add footer, cast as string in case non-string set\n\t\t\t$body .= (string) $this->footer;\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\/\/ Determin e-mail type and add body\n\t\t\tif ($this->html) {\n\t\t\t\t$this->_mail->setBodyHtml($body);\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\t$this->_mail->setBodyText($body);\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\/\/ Send e-mail\n\t\t\t$this->_mail->send();\n\t\t}\n\t\t\n\t\t\/\/ Call parent, will set shutdown to true\n\t\tparent::shutdown();\n\t}\n}\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-23T12:28:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-23T12:28:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22618",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Should you may be a little more careful with the \"html\" data member?\n\nFor example, if I set the \"html\" data member to some random object, won't that cause the setBodyHtml() call to barf somewhere along the way?\n\nMaybe do an is_scalar() check before that \"if ($this->html)\" check in shutdown()?  That or cast it to a string as you do with \"header\" and \"footer\".\n\nThough, personally, I'd tend to prefer getHtml() and setHtml() instead of public data members.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-23T15:11:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-23T15:11:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22619",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ah, nevermind about my previous comment.  It's a non-issue due to the ternary expression for setting $body above.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-23T15:13:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-23T15:13:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22622",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I had thought about that but decided it shouldn't be a big deal. If like you say, the html property is set to an object, the if statement should just count it as true. The value is not actually used anywhere.\n\nI also like to force getters and setters but it also seems to be the \"Zend\" way to keep things rather open. After all, PHP is supposed to be very flexible with their data types. This is an example of why it really doesn't matter. It's the users fault if they set html to anything other than boolean. [End rant] :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-24T05:56:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-24T05:56:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22623",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Eh, personally, I tend to agree with making \"header\", \"footer\", and \"html\" public data members.  I'm by no means a Jedi Master on Zend Framework's preferences when it comes to these types of decisions, but for the sake of a clear interface, I'd prefer to see the getters and setters rather than have willy nilly access to the public data members.\n\nQuick, rough stat from trunk: out of 1,081 *.php files, I see that only 86 have public data members, which would lead me to believe that this isn't a common practice.  A large portion of those 86 come from Zend_Form and Zend_Service.\n\nAgain, this would just be my personal preference for the sake of a clear interface.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-24T06:12:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-24T06:12:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22625",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, I'm glad they don't use public members throughout the framework. I like how you added the stats in there. :) I am very new to ZF and just started to work with it. The log was the first thing I am working on and this is what was missing.\n\nAlso, digging into HTML in e-mail a bit more, I wonder if setting a HTML body and text body would be a nice feature. Then set the $_mail->setType() to Zend_Mime::MULTIPART_ALTERNATIVE. That way the e-mail client can choose which to use. Of course the HTML would have to be striped for the text body. Or is this getting into more than is worth? :D Will attach a new patch with this feature. Are these patches close to what you were thinking?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-24T07:49:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-24T07:49:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22626",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Also, I see that this issue tracker ticket was opened in May 2007, while I proposed Zend_Log_Writer_Mail in January 2008.\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFPROP\/Zend_Log_Writer_Mail\n\nMaybe there's some overlap here; just wanted to point out the parallel thinking going on in this area.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bdeshong",
                        "name": "bdeshong",
                        "displayName": "Brian DeShong",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-24T07:50:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-24T07:50:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22627",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=panman",
                        "name": "panman",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Panning",
